commit.message:
Add cvar to enable/disable directwrite text editor backend

Apparently it doesn't support non-ttf fonts. Should fix #1646

Update issue templates

Don't use 'render:' attribute for textarea sections (except crash info) since we want these to be formatted and not just shown as plaintext

Map editor 3d floors support in 3d mode (#1358)

* Adapt eevee's old WIP 3d floors code to the 3.2.0 codebase

Some unrelated changes were ignored but hopefully I haven't missed anything important

Seems to work ok for the most part, at least for basic, solid 3d floors (swimmable/transparent ones are another matter, plenty of bugs there)

I've also added the cvar 'map_process_3d_floors' which will enable/disable 3d floor processing

* Fix 3d-mode segmentation faults by zero-initializing visible flats array (#1376)

The array was being used uninitialized causing random crashes

* Fix editing of 3d floors properties not being correctly forwarded to the control sector (#1381)

It was actually being forwarded to the target sector from the control sector, causing ambiguous issues like when you changing the 3d floor height/textures you were changing the ones in the sector it was over instead.

* Add support for Srb2's Floor Over Floors (3d floors) (#1438)

* Add option to enable 'experimental' 3d floors preview  (with a warning)

In the Map Editor > 3d Mode preferences page

Also changed the cvar to be false by default

---------

Co-authored-by: FlykeSpice <69917355+FlykeSpice@users.noreply.github.com>

Map editor 3d floors support in 3d mode (#1358)

Some unrelated changes were ignored but hopefully I haven't missed anything important

Seems to work ok for the most part, at least for basic, solid 3d floors (swimmable/transparent ones are another matter, plenty of bugs there)

I've also added the cvar 'map_process_3d_floors' which will enable/disable 3d floor processing

* Fix 3d-mode segmentation faults by zero-initializing visible flats array (#1376)

The array was being used uninitialized causing random crashes

* Fix editing of 3d floors properties not being correctly forwarded to the control sector (#1381)

It was actually being forwarded to the target sector from the control sector, causing ambiguous issues like when you changing the 3d floor height/textures you were changing the ones in the sector it was over instead.

* Add support for Srb2's Floor Over Floors (3d floors) (#1438)

* Add option to enable 'experimental' 3d floors preview  (with a warning)

In the Map Editor > 3d Mode preferences page

Also changed the cvar to be false by default

commit.message:
Replace deprecated wxBitmap methods (#1561)

wxBitmap::SetWidth and wxBitmap::SetHeight have been deprecated since
wxWidgets 3.1.2 and are removed in the current v3.3 development trunk.
Use wxBitmap::GetSubBitmap as an alternative.
